13:09.259 --> 13:12.760
I think the word you're
looking for is "bravo."

13:14.029 --> 13:15.930
Okay, you leave the room
and find yourself

13:15.932 --> 13:18.366
standing before a pool
of melted snowmen.

13:18.368 --> 13:19.617
Melted snowmen?

13:19.619 --> 13:21.786
Are there carrots
and lumps of coal in the water?

13:21.788 --> 13:23.071
I don't know.
What's the difference?

13:23.073 --> 13:25.290
It's a game of
the imagination, Leonard.

13:25.292 --> 13:26.274
Paint a picture.

13:26.276 --> 13:27.325
Fine.

13:27.327 --> 13:28.827
You leave the room
and find yourself

13:28.829 --> 13:30.545
standing before a pool
of melted snowmen.

13:30.547 --> 13:32.446
There are carrots and
lumps of coal in the water.

13:32.448 --> 13:35.300
What happened to the
top hats and the corncob pipes?

13:35.302 --> 13:37.051
You see those, too.

13:37.053 --> 13:39.787
Oh, it's like I'm really there.

13:41.957 --> 13:45.459
I gotta tell you, this-this is
the most holiday fun I've had

13:45.461 --> 13:48.629
since my therapist changed
my anxiety medication

13:48.631 --> 13:51.465
and I stopped caring about
the blood in my stool.

13:53.819 --> 13:55.803
Good story.

13:56.739 --> 13:58.022
What are you drinking there?

13:58.024 --> 13:59.073
Little eggnog?

13:59.075 --> 14:00.325
Yes.

14:00.327 --> 14:01.609
What, is there a problem?

14:01.611 --> 14:04.662
No, it's nice to see you
enjoying a holiday beverage.

14:04.664 --> 14:05.813
Pretty Christmasy.

14:05.815 --> 14:08.249
Since when is eggnog
a Christmas drink?

14:09.651 --> 14:11.286
Eggs are available
all year 'round.

14:11.288 --> 14:14.539
I've been known to
enjoy this poolside.

14:14.541 --> 14:16.624
Come on, Sheldon.

14:16.626 --> 14:18.659
You know all the Christmas
stories, and the carols,

14:18.661 --> 14:20.879
you've got an eggnog
mustache going on there.

14:20.881 --> 14:22.163
Just admit it.

14:22.165 --> 14:23.765
You're getting
a little Yuletide spirit.

14:23.767 --> 14:25.266
Oh, don't be silly.

14:25.268 --> 14:28.186
Christmas is a bunch of baloney
created by the tinsel industry.

14:29.021 --> 14:31.005
Why is this so important to you?

14:31.007 --> 14:33.107
Honestly, because I had enough
crappy Christmases as a kid

14:33.109 --> 14:35.193
and I'm tired of you
sucking the joy out of them now.

14:35.195 --> 14:37.028
What was so bad
about them?

14:37.030 --> 14:39.948
I grew up in a house
full of crazy academics.

14:39.950 --> 14:42.150
Instead of leaving Santa
milk and cookies,

14:42.152 --> 14:44.452
we had to leave him
a research paper.

14:46.155 --> 14:48.356
And in the morning,
you could tell he'd been there

14:48.358 --> 14:50.124
because the paper
would be graded.

14:51.293 --> 14:52.794
No wonder you love Christmas.

14:52.796 --> 14:55.046
That sounds amazing.

14:55.048 --> 14:57.031
It wasn't amazing.

14:57.033 --> 14:59.867
I got a C-minus
four years in a row.

14:59.869 --> 15:01.369
Yeah, I'm familiar
with your work.

15:01.371 --> 15:02.720
C-minus was your gift.

15:05.808 --> 15:08.559
Amy, I'm really sorry.

15:08.561 --> 15:10.311
I didn't mean to upset you.

15:10.313 --> 15:11.646
It's fine.

15:11.648 --> 15:13.881
I'm used to being the girl
who never gets looked at twice.

15:13.883 --> 15:16.901
I didn't have my first kiss
till I was 22,

15:16.903 --> 15:20.054
and the guy only did it so
I'd give him back his insulin.

15:22.241 --> 15:26.444
Sometimes the pancreas wants
what the pancreas wants.

15:27.279 --> 15:28.613
Forget it.

15:28.615 --> 15:30.164
I don't expect
you guys to understand.

15:30.166 --> 15:31.749
I understand.

15:31.751 --> 15:33.751
In seventh grade,
I played Spin the Bottle

15:33.753 --> 15:35.403
and it landed on Alina Shankar.

15:35.405 --> 15:37.038
She said if I came near her,

15:37.040 --> 15:39.657
she would break
the bottle and cut me.

15:39.659 --> 15:41.209
You think that's bad?

15:41.211 --> 15:43.244
In college, I passed out
at a frat party

15:43.246 --> 15:45.680
and woke up with
more clothes on.

15:49.802 --> 15:51.469
Sometimes I get so lonely,

15:51.471 --> 15:53.855
I sit on my left hand
until it goes numb,

15:53.857 --> 15:56.107
then I put it in
my right hand and pretend

15:56.109 --> 15:58.592
I'm holding hands
with another person.

15:58.594 --> 16:01.562
I do that, too.

16:01.564 --> 16:03.764
Sometimes the left hand
tries to cop a feel.

16:05.567 --> 16:07.785
And I let it.

16:09.371 --> 16:12.206
It's kind of nice
to talk to someone

16:12.208 --> 16:14.459
who understands what
it feels like to be alone.

16:14.461 --> 16:16.744
It is, isn't it?

16:16.746 --> 16:18.612
But you're not alone anymore.
Now you've got Sheldon.

16:18.614 --> 16:19.914
I do.

16:19.916 --> 16:22.967
And don't worry, someday
you'll have somebody, too.

16:22.969 --> 16:24.335
Thank you.

16:24.337 --> 16:28.256
I hope she's half as
lovely and amazing as you are.

16:29.124 --> 16:31.676
Thank you, Rajesh.

16:31.678 --> 16:33.594
He wants me, I'm good.
We can go now.

16:35.964 --> 16:36.981
Damn it.

16:36.983 --> 16:38.349
What?

16:38.351 --> 16:40.184
Now that I know
she doesn't like me,

16:40.186 --> 16:42.286
I'm kind of into her.

16:43.472 --> 16:45.556
All right.

16:45.558 --> 16:49.394
I think I cracked the code
to lower the drawbridge.

16:49.396 --> 16:50.811
Great.
Let's do it.

16:57.753 --> 16:59.203
The drawbridge is lowering.

17:05.544 --> 17:07.045
My carpal tunnel's acting up.

17:07.047 --> 17:08.463
Play through
the pain!

17:19.674 --> 17:21.692
You did it!
The drawbridge is down.

17:21.694 --> 17:23.277
You cross the chasm

17:23.279 --> 17:26.114
and find yourself in
a small dungeon room.

17:26.116 --> 17:28.766
And in the corner,
chained to the wall,

17:28.768 --> 17:31.352
you see a bloodied and beaten
Santa Claus.

17:31.354 --> 17:35.022
He says, "Ho, ho, help me."

17:35.024 --> 17:37.542
Yes, we found Santa!

17:37.544 --> 17:39.544
Christmas is saved!

17:39.546 --> 17:42.213
Don't ever tell
my mother I said that.

17:43.298 --> 17:45.199
I take out
my skeleton key

17:45.201 --> 17:46.968
and run to Santa
to unchain him.

17:46.970 --> 17:48.970
But first, I cast
a spell of paralysis

17:48.972 --> 17:51.422
on Stuart and Howard.
Wait, what are you doing?

17:51.424 --> 17:53.741
You can't talk;
you're paralyzed.

17:53.743 --> 17:57.678
I get right up in Santa's
big, fat face and say...

17:57.680 --> 17:59.213
Well, well, well,

17:59.215 --> 18:01.899
jolly old Saint Nick,
we meet again.

18:01.901 --> 18:03.584
Yeah, I believe
the last time we spoke

18:03.586 --> 18:06.654
was in the Baybrook Mall
in Galveston, Texas,

18:06.656 --> 18:08.906
when I was five years old,
isn't that right?

18:08.908 --> 18:11.125
Uh, okay.

18:11.127 --> 18:12.560
My mother
dragged me there

18:12.562 --> 18:14.445
and she plopped me
down on your lap

18:14.447 --> 18:16.747
and you asked me
what I wanted for Christmas.

18:16.749 --> 18:18.699
And I told you "my Pop-Pop,"

18:18.701 --> 18:21.235
because that was the year
my grandfather died.

18:21.237 --> 18:24.071
I missed him
and I wanted him back.

18:24.923 --> 18:27.425
This is weird, right?

18:30.429 --> 18:32.346
Pop-Pop was the only one
in my family

18:32.348 --> 18:34.215
who encouraged me
to pursue science.

18:34.217 --> 18:36.417
But you didn't bring
him back, did you?

18:36.419 --> 18:39.137
Instead, I got Lincoln Logs.

18:39.139 --> 18:43.090
Well, you can build a lot of
neat things out of Lincoln Logs,

18:43.092 --> 18:44.942
but Pop-Pop ain't one of 'em.

18:44.944 --> 18:48.262
And now you're here
asking me for something--

18:48.264 --> 18:49.597
to save you.

18:49.599 --> 18:53.934
Well, sorry, Mr. Kringle,
but today's not your day.

18:53.936 --> 18:55.486
I'm leaving you here to rot,

18:55.488 --> 18:58.156
and I hope the ogres
feast on your bones.

18:58.158 --> 19:01.709
I take the skeleton key,
and I toss it into the chasm,

19:01.711 --> 19:03.711
and on the way out, I give Santa

19:03.713 --> 19:06.747
a swift kick in his
bowl full of jelly!

19:08.050 --> 19:10.468
Okay.

19:10.470 --> 19:13.671
So Wolowitz and Stuart
are paralyzed, Santa's dead,

19:13.673 --> 19:17.124
and I picked this over
having sex with my girlfriend.

19:35.283 --> 19:36.583
Santa?

19:36.585 --> 19:41.071
Oh, hello, Sheldon.

19:41.073 --> 19:43.290
You should be asleep.

19:43.292 --> 19:45.408
Well, then, you shouldn't have
jingle bells on your boots.

19:45.410 --> 19:46.660
Oh...

19:47.461 --> 19:50.113
I've been wanting
to talk to you.

19:50.115 --> 19:54.301
I'm sorry I disappointed you
when you were a little boy.

19:55.102 --> 19:58.788
I-I can do a lot
of magical things,

19:58.790 --> 20:03.343
but unfortunately bringing your
Pop-Pop back isn't one of them.

20:04.178 --> 20:06.296
I understand.

20:06.298 --> 20:09.683
But I-I do have
something special for you.

20:10.534 --> 20:12.302
Close your eyes.

20:14.155 --> 20:16.639
Oh, I hope it's a train.

20:16.641 --> 20:19.826
Oh, it's better than a train.

20:19.828 --> 20:23.079
Two trains?

20:23.081 --> 20:24.814
Better.

20:24.816 --> 20:27.000
I'm getting three trains.

20:28.836 --> 20:30.870
Okay, open 'em.

20:34.425 --> 20:36.659
This is for leaving me
in the dungeon

20:36.661 --> 20:39.512
to be eaten alive by ogres!

20:39.514 --> 20:40.964
Wait, uh, uh, hang on.

20:40.966 --> 20:42.048
I-In my defense...

20:42.050 --> 20:44.551
Ho, ho, ho, ya big dork!

